value.title: Pence urges Biden administration to have ‘eternal vigilance’ in standing up to China
value.excerpt: In one of his final public appearances before leaving the White House next  week, Vice President Mike Pence urged the Biden administration to exercise "eternal vigilance," especially when it comes to U.S.-China relations.

value.title: Trump finishes with worst first term approval rating ever
value.excerpt: Poll of the week: A new Quinnipiac University poll finds that President Donald Trump's approval rating stands at 33%, while his disapproval is at 60%.

value.title: Census battle ends as Trump administration gives up on excluding undocumented from apportionment
value.excerpt: A high-stakes six-month battle over who should be counted for representation in Congress ended quietly in a judge’s chamber Friday night when the Trump administration agreed not to release any population numbers from the 2020 Census for congressional apportionment or redistricting before the president leaves office.

value.title: Trump trial pending, McConnell calls it ‘vote of conscience’

value.title: Despite Trump administration promise, government has no more 'reserve' 2nd vaccine doses
value.excerpt: Hopes of a surge in Covid-19 vaccine shipments under a new policy to release second doses held in reserve appear to be evaporating -- with the revelation that those doses have already been distributed, contrary to recent indications by the Trump administration.

value.title: Trump receives Morocco's highest award for Middle East work: official

value.title: FBI agent in Trump-Russia's request for 'validation' of Steele reporting denied, left Crossfire Hurricane
value.excerpt: An agent involved in the FBI’s original Trump-Russia case left the Crossfire Hurricane team amid a “professional disagreement” with Bill Priestap, after the former assistant director of counterintelligence denied his request for an “enhanced validation review” of Christopher Steele’s reporting.

value.title: Trump retreats from his job, and Pence fills the void as ‘acting’ president
value.excerpt: With President Trump isolated in the White House since the Jan. 6 Capitol riot, Vice President Mike Pence increasingly fills the void in their waning days in office.

value.title: Trump plans to depart Washington Inauguration Day morning, while Pence, Harris speak
value.excerpt: President Trump plans to make the unprecedented move to depart the White House next Wednesday morning, just before President-elect Joe Biden's inauguration.
